A metalens was manufactured based on plasmonic nanoslits3 or antenna4 using metals that can focus light to the subwavelength region and easily change the phase of light depending on the size and shape of the nanostructure. However, because the absorption loss of the metal reduces the efficiency of the lens, the metal was replaced with a dielectric material with relatively little absorption loss. Dielectric meta-atoms act like waveguides and achieve phase accumulation using the following equation2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
